propDescriptions.classes: Override or extend the styles applied to the component. See CSS API below for more details.
propDescriptions.disableTypography: If true, the children won't be wrapped by a Typography component. This can be useful to render an alternative Typography variant by wrapping the children (or primary) text, and optional secondary text with the Typography component.
propDescriptions.inset: If true, the children are indented. This should be used if there is no left avatar or left icon.
propDescriptions.primaryTypographyProps: These props will be forwarded to the primary typography component (as long as disableTypography is not true).
propDescriptions.secondaryTypographyProps: These props will be forwarded to the secondary typography component (as long as disableTypography is not true).
propDescriptions.sx: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details.

root.description: Styles applied to the root element.
